scripts.comment: This exampla shows you how to draw a line of 24 mm (~1inch) lenght

block.comment: repeat the block inside several times to get a line stitched

scripts.comment: the reset command puts the cursor back to the start, corrects the direction and clears the stage
"move 10 steps" to define the length of a single stitch. The number of steps determines the size of the individual stitch. 10 steps = 2 mm stitch 20 steps = 4 mm stitch
